[{"location":"man/check.html#Introduction","page":"d_check.py","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/check.html","page":"d_check.py","title":"d_check.py","text":"It is a Python script. It is only compatible with Python 3.x. The purpose of this script is to check whether the lines in a given file are ended with blanks.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/check.html","page":"d_check.py","title":"d_check.py","text":"note: Note\nThis script should be used by the developer only.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/check.html#Usage","page":"d_check.py","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/check.html","page":"d_check.py","title":"d_check.py","text":"$ ./d_check.py file_name","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html#Introduction","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"It is a shell script. The purpose of this script is to scan a file or directory, and then replace some characters with given characters. So we name it as d_sar.sh (Scan And Replace). We can use it to preprocess many atom.config.in or solver.ctqmc.in files at the same time.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"note: Note\nThis script should be used by the developer only.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html#Usage","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"$ ./d_sar.sh","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"Before you start to use this shell script, you have to check and edit carefully the string match pattern (see L28 in d_sar.sh).","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"For macOS system, the grammar for sed is (we don't generate backup)","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"sed -i '' ...","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"However, for Linux-based system, the grammar for sed is","category":"page"},{"location":"man/sar.html","page":"d_sar.sh","title":"d_sar.sh","text":"sed -i ...","category":"page"},{"location":"man/clean.html#Introduction","page":"d_clean.py","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/clean.html","page":"d_clean.py","title":"d_clean.py","text":"It is a Python script. It is only compatible with Python 3.x. The purpose of this script is to clean the dull .DS_Store files in the macOS system.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/clean.html","page":"d_clean.py","title":"d_clean.py","text":"note: Note\nThis script should be used by the developer only.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/clean.html","page":"d_clean.py","title":"d_clean.py","text":"info: Info\nIt seems that the .DS_Store files only appear in the macOS system.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/clean.html#Usage","page":"d_clean.py","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/clean.html","page":"d_clean.py","title":"d_clean.py","text":"$ ./d_clean.py directory_name","category":"page"},{"location":"intro.html#Features","page":"About hdev","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"intro.html","page":"About hdev","title":"About hdev","text":"Shell scripts\nCreate archive for repo branch (d_arch.sh)\nFix @rpath problem (d_rpath.sh)\nSearch and replace (d_sar.sh)\nGet rid of trailing whitespaces (d_trim.sh)\nPython scripts\nCheck whether the lines are ended with blanks (d_check.py)\nRemove the dull .DS_Store files (d_clean.py)","category":"page"},{"location":"intro.html#Author","page":"About hdev","title":"Author","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"intro.html","page":"About hdev","title":"About hdev","text":"Li Huang\nInstitute of Materials, China Academy of Engineering Physics, Sichuan Jiangyou, PRC\nemail: huangli at caep.cn","category":"page"},{"location":"man/rpath.html#Introduction","page":"d_rpath.sh","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/rpath.html","page":"d_rpath.sh","title":"d_rpath.sh","text":"It is a shell script. The purpose of this script is to fix the @rpath symbol in the executable program in the macOS system.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/rpath.html","page":"d_rpath.sh","title":"d_rpath.sh","text":"note: Note\nThis script should be used by the developer only.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/rpath.html#Usage","page":"d_rpath.sh","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/rpath.html","page":"d_rpath.sh","title":"d_rpath.sh","text":"$ ./d_rpath.sh file_name","category":"page"},{"location":"man/rpath.html","page":"d_rpath.sh","title":"d_rpath.sh","text":"Perhaps before you use this script to fix your program, you have to modify this script to correct the path for Intel MKL. Specially, you have to correct L20 in d_rpath.sh.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/rpath.html","page":"d_rpath.sh","title":"d_rpath.sh","text":"20 MKL=/opt/intel/compilers_and_libraries_2017.0.102/mac/mkl/lib","category":"page"},{"location":"man/trim.html#Introduction","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/trim.html","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"d_trim.sh","text":"It is a shell script. The purpose of this script is to remove the trailing whitespaces in the given file.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/trim.html","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"d_trim.sh","text":"note: Note\nThis script should be used by the developer only.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/trim.html#Usage","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/trim.html","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"d_trim.sh","text":"$ ./d_trim.sh file_name","category":"page"},{"location":"man/trim.html","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"d_trim.sh","text":"For macOS system, the grammar for sed is (we don't generate backup)","category":"page"},{"location":"man/trim.html","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"d_trim.sh","text":"$ sed -i '' ...","category":"page"},{"location":"man/trim.html","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"d_trim.sh","text":"However, for Linux-based system, the grammar for sed is","category":"page"},{"location":"man/trim.html","page":"d_trim.sh","title":"d_trim.sh","text":"$ sed -i ...","category":"page"},{"location":"man/arch.html#Introduction","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/arch.html","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"d_arch.sh","text":"It is a shell script. The purpose of this script is to create archive of files (in the working directory) from the current repo branch.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/arch.html","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"d_arch.sh","text":"The name of the output archive should like this:","category":"page"},{"location":"man/arch.html","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"d_arch.sh","text":"iqist_43e2cbb_1441276643.tar.gz","category":"page"},{"location":"man/arch.html","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"d_arch.sh","text":"Here 43e2cbb is the abbreviated commit hash, 1441276643 is the UNIX timestamp when this commit was committed, and iqist is the code name which is provided by the users.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/arch.html","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"d_arch.sh","text":"note: Note\nThis script should be used by the developer only.","category":"page"},{"location":"man/arch.html#Usage","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"man/arch.html","page":"d_arch.sh","title":"d_arch.sh","text":"$ ./d_arch.sh code_name","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#hdev","page":"Welcome","title":"hdev","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Welcome","title":"Welcome","text":"A collection of useful shell and python scripts","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Welcome","title":"Welcome","text":"info: Info\nThank you for using hdev. This documentation will help you to be familiar with and explore the hdev toolkit. It is just compatible with hdev v1.0.4-devel.250923.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Welcome","title":"Welcome","text":"note: Note\nThe hdev toolkit is used by myself to deal with some minor issues. It is not a general purpose toolkit.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Welcome","title":"Welcome","text":"warning: Warning\nThe hdev toolkit is in heavy development. Please use it at your own risk. If you encounter any bugs or troubles, or require new features, please consult me directly: huangli at caep.cn","category":"page"}]
